{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1197,"text":"War has been a part of my life\nsince I can remember."},{"time":4811,"text":"I was born in Afghanistan,\njust six months after the Soviets invaded,"},{"time":9526,"text":"and even though I was too young\nto understand what was happening,"},{"time":12831,"text":"I had a deep sense of the suffering\nand the fear around me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17219,"text":"Those early experiences had a major impact\non how I now think about war and conflict."},{"time":23049,"text":"I learned that when people\nhave a fundamental issue at stake,"},{"time":26511,"text":"for most of them,"},{"time":27787,"text":"giving in is not an option."},{"time":29971,"text":"For these types conflicts --"},{"time":31607,"text":"when people's rights are violated,"},{"time":33416,"text":"when their countries are occupied,"},{"time":35210,"text":"when they're oppressed and humiliated --"},{"time":37452,"text":"they need a powerful way\nto resist and to fight back."},{"time":41308,"text":"Which means that no matter how destructive\nand terrible violence is,"},{"time":45595,"text":"if people see it as their only choice,"},{"time":48043,"text":"they will use it."},{"time":50074,"text":"Most of us are concerned\nwith the level of violence in the world."},{"time":54045,"text":"But we're not going to end war"},{"time":55523,"text":"by telling people\nthat violence is morally wrong."},{"time":58883,"text":"Instead, we must offer them a tool"},{"time":61306,"text":"that's at least as powerful\nand as effective as violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65574,"text":"This is the work I do."},{"time":67717,"text":"For the past 13 years,"},{"time":69280,"text":"I've been teaching people"},{"time":70589,"text":"in some of the most difficult\nsituations around the world"},{"time":73721,"text":"how they can use nonviolent\nstruggle to conduct conflict."},{"time":78113,"text":"Most people associate this type of action\nwith Gandhi and Martin Luther King."},{"time":83589,"text":"But people have been using\nnonviolent action for thousands of years."},{"time":87831,"text":"In fact, most of the rights\nthat we have today in this country --"},{"time":92187,"text":"as women,"},{"time":93362,"text":"as minorities,"},{"time":94537,"text":"as workers,"},{"time":95909,"text":"as people of different sexual orientations"},{"time":98499,"text":"and citizens concerned\nwith the environment --"},{"time":100981,"text":"these rights weren't handed to us."},{"time":103226,"text":"They were won by people\nwho fought for them"},{"time":105410,"text":"and who sacrificed for them."},{"time":107256,"text":"But because we haven't learned\nfrom this history,"},{"time":109800,"text":"nonviolent struggle as a technique\nis widely misunderstood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114488,"text":"I met recently with a group\nof Ethiopian activists,"},{"time":117634,"text":"and they told me something\nthat I hear a lot."},{"time":120808,"text":"They said they'd already\ntried nonviolent action,"},{"time":123158,"text":"and it hadn't worked."},{"time":124600,"text":"Years ago they held a protest."},{"time":126960,"text":"The government arrested everyone,\nand that was the end of that."},{"time":131302,"text":"The idea that nonviolent struggle\nis equivalent to street protests"},{"time":135286,"text":"is a real problem."},{"time":137204,"text":"Because although protests can be a great\nway to show that people want change,"},{"time":141628,"text":"on their own, they don't\nactually create change --"},{"time":144522,"text":"at least change that is fundamental."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146514,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147726,"text":"Powerful opponents are not going to give\npeople what they want"},{"time":150859,"text":"just because they asked nicely ..."},{"time":153519,"text":"or even not so nicely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155420,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156577,"text":"Nonviolent struggle works\nby destroying an opponent,"},{"time":160018,"text":"not physically,"},{"time":161354,"text":"but by identifying the institutions\nthat an opponent needs to survive,"},{"time":165788,"text":"and then denying them\nthose sources of power."},{"time":168470,"text":"Nonviolent activists\ncan neutralize the military"},{"time":171258,"text":"by causing soldiers to defect."},{"time":173506,"text":"They can disrupt the economy\nthrough strikes and boycotts."},{"time":177190,"text":"And they can challenge\ngovernment propaganda"},{"time":179516,"text":"by creating alternative media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181829,"text":"There are a variety of methods\nthat can be used to do this."},{"time":185384,"text":"My colleague and mentor, Gene Sharp,"},{"time":188200,"text":"has identified 198 methods\nof nonviolent action."},{"time":194186,"text":"And protest is only one."},{"time":196376,"text":"Let me give you a recent example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198885,"text":"Until a few months ago,"},{"time":200378,"text":"Guatemala was ruled\nby corrupt former military officials"},{"time":203619,"text":"with ties to organized crime."},{"time":206071,"text":"People were generally aware of this,"},{"time":207888,"text":"but most of them felt powerless\nto do anything about it --"},{"time":212401,"text":"until one group of citizens,\njust 12 regular people,"},{"time":216506,"text":"put out a call on Facebook\nto their friends"},{"time":219272,"text":"to meet in the central plaza,\nholding signs with a message:"},{"time":223046,"text":"\"Renuncia YA\" --"},{"time":225024,"text":"resign already."},{"time":227199,"text":"To their surprise,"},{"time":228632,"text":"30,000 people showed up."},{"time":231045,"text":"They stayed there for months\nas protests spread throughout the country."},{"time":234932,"text":"At one point,"},{"time":236112,"text":"the organizers delivered hundreds of eggs\nto various government buildings"},{"time":240324,"text":"with a message:"},{"time":241960,"text":"\"If you don't have the huevos\" --"},{"time":243870,"text":"the balls --"},{"time":245100,"text":"\"to stop corrupt candidates\nfrom running for office,"},{"time":248178,"text":"you can borrow ours.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":249660,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":251343,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256469,"text":"President Molina responded"},{"time":258012,"text":"by vowing that he would never step down."},{"time":260674,"text":"And the activists realized\nthat they couldn't just keep protesting"},{"time":264299,"text":"and ask the president to resign."},{"time":266337,"text":"They needed to leave him no choice."},{"time":268793,"text":"So they organized a general strike,"},{"time":270748,"text":"in which people throughout\nthe country refused to work."},{"time":273419,"text":"In Guatemala City alone,"},{"time":274845,"text":"over 400 businesses\nand schools shut their doors."},{"time":278367,"text":"Meanwhile,"},{"time":279572,"text":"farmers throughout the country\nblocked major roads."},{"time":282225,"text":"Within five days,"},{"time":283727,"text":"the president,"},{"time":284928,"text":"along with dozens of other\ngovernment officials,"},{"time":287675,"text":"resigned already."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289168,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293475,"text":"I've been greatly inspired"},{"time":295102,"text":"by the creativity and bravery\nof people using nonviolent action"},{"time":299029,"text":"in nearly every country in the world."},{"time":301718,"text":"For example,"},{"time":302893,"text":"recently a group of activists in Uganda"},{"time":305474,"text":"released a crate of pigs in the streets."},{"time":308096,"text":"You can see here that the police\nare confused about what to do with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311558,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312618,"text":"The pigs were painted\nthe color of the ruling party."},{"time":315617,"text":"One pig was even wearing a hat,"},{"time":317919,"text":"a hat that people recognized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320321,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":322264,"text":"Activists around the world\nare getting better at grabbing headlines,"},{"time":325657,"text":"but these isolated actions do very little"},{"time":328344,"text":"if they're not part of a larger strategy."},{"time":330914,"text":"A general wouldn't march\nhis troops into battle"},{"time":333177,"text":"unless he had a plan to win the war."},{"time":335332,"text":"Yet this is how most of the world's\nnonviolent movements operate."},{"time":338896,"text":"Nonviolent struggle is just as complex\nas military warfare,"},{"time":343240,"text":"if not more."},{"time":344462,"text":"Its participants must be well-trained\nand have clear objectives,"},{"time":348681,"text":"and its leaders must have a strategy\nof how to achieve those objectives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353242,"text":"The technique of war has been developed\nover thousands of years"},{"time":356532,"text":"with massive resources"},{"time":358103,"text":"and some of our best minds\ndedicated to understanding"},{"time":361373,"text":"and improving how it works."},{"time":363608,"text":"Meanwhile, nonviolent struggle\nis rarely systematically studied,"},{"time":368214,"text":"and even though the number is growing,"},{"time":370248,"text":"there are still only a few dozen people\nin the world who are teaching it."},{"time":374849,"text":"This is dangerous,"},{"time":376166,"text":"because we now know that our old\napproaches of dealing with conflict"},{"time":380358,"text":"are not adequate for the new\nchallenges that we're facing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383800,"text":"The US government recently admitted"},{"time":385907,"text":"that it's in a stalemate\nin its war against ISIS."},{"time":389318,"text":"But what most people don't know"},{"time":391086,"text":"is that people have stood up to ISIS\nusing nonviolent action."},{"time":395120,"text":"When ISIS captured Mosul in June 2014,"},{"time":398954,"text":"they announced that they were putting\nin place a new public school curriculum,"},{"time":402709,"text":"based on their own extremist ideology."},{"time":405556,"text":"But on the first day of school,"},{"time":407672,"text":"not a single child showed up."},{"time":410222,"text":"Parents simply refused to send them."},{"time":413068,"text":"They told journalists they would rather\nhomeschool their children"},{"time":416284,"text":"than to have them brainwashed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418689,"text":"This is an example\nof just one act of defiance"},{"time":421722,"text":"in just one city."},{"time":423659,"text":"But what if it was coordinated"},{"time":425128,"text":"with the dozens of other acts\nof nonviolent resistance"},{"time":427774,"text":"that have taken place against ISIS?"},{"time":429853,"text":"What if the parents' boycott\nwas part of a larger strategy"},{"time":433312,"text":"to identify and cut off the resources\nthat ISIS needs to function;"},{"time":438157,"text":"the skilled labor needed to produce food;"},{"time":440677,"text":"the engineers needed\nto extract and refine oil;"},{"time":444290,"text":"the media infrastructure\nand communications networks"},{"time":446907,"text":"and transportation systems,"},{"time":448904,"text":"and the local businesses\nthat ISIS relies on?"},{"time":451911,"text":"It may be difficult\nto imagine defeating ISIS"},{"time":455056,"text":"with action that is nonviolent."},{"time":457511,"text":"But it's time we challenge\nthe way we think about conflict"},{"time":460643,"text":"and the choices we have in facing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464194,"text":"Here's an idea worth spreading:"},{"time":466489,"text":"let's learn more about where\nnonviolent action has worked"},{"time":469668,"text":"and how we can make it more powerful,"},{"time":472209,"text":"just like we do with other\nsystems and technologies"},{"time":475277,"text":"that are constantly being refined\nto better meet human needs."},{"time":479446,"text":"It may be that we can improve\nnonviolent action"},{"time":482929,"text":"to a point where it is increasingly\nused in place of war."},{"time":486838,"text":"Violence as a tool of conflict\ncould then be abandoned"},{"time":490937,"text":"in the same way that bows and arrows were,"},{"time":493368,"text":"because we have replaced them\nwith weapons that are more effective."},{"time":497427,"text":"With human innovation, we can make\nnonviolent struggle more powerful"},{"time":502330,"text":"than the newest and latest\ntechnologies of war."},{"time":506010,"text":"The greatest hope for humanity\nlies not in condemning violence"},{"time":510497,"text":"but in making violence obsolete."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514365,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515540,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}